"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-07-17-france-accused-shameful-decision-days-paris-olympics-21238317\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Francehas been accused of 'racistgenderdiscrimination' over the decision to bar its athletes from wearing thehijabat theParisOlympics.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 134, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is the latest controversysurrounding the games,which have already come under fire for theRiver Seine's water qualityand calls to veto the participation of Russia and Israel.\", \"from\": 136, \"to\": 312, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 234, \"end\": 239, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999997383274946, \"rank\": 2.511692880881824e-07, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 294, \"end\": 300, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.999999837973532, \"rank\": 9.483596672550918e-08, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 305, \"end\": 311, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 0.9999999956930878, \"rank\": 2.8884266258152203e-09, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the\\u00a0International Olympic Committee\\u00a0has said athletes would be permitted to wear the scarf without restrictions, France has imposed its own ban that applies solely to its own athletes taking part in Olympic andParalympicgames.\", \"from\": 314, \"to\": 546, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 324, \"end\": 355, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 433, \"end\": 439, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999815433468716, \"rank\": 1.8045001202915305e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is now less than 10 days untilthe Olympicskicks off on July 26.\", \"from\": 548, \"to\": 614, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But despite calls for the discriminatory policy to be overturned, there is no sign France will budge.\", \"from\": 615, \"to\": 716, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 698, \"end\": 704, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999815433468716, \"rank\": 1.8045001202915305e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Basketball player\\u00a0H\\u00e9l\\u00e8ne B\\u00e2, co-founder of Basket pour Toutes (Basketball for All),\\u00a0said this will be a 'shameful moment' for the country.\", \"from\": 718, \"to\": 856, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She said: 'It is a clear violation of the Olympic charter, values and provisions, and an infringement on our fundamental rights and freedoms\\u2026'  A 32-page report\\u00a0from Amnesty International published on Tuesday reveals the devastating impact of the restriction on Muslim women and girls at all levels of French sport.\", \"from\": 858, \"to\": 1173, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1024, \"end\": 1045, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amnesty_International\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.511111018029464e-15, \"text\": \"Amnesty International\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amnesty_International\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amnesty_International\"}, {\"begin\": 1120, \"end\": 1126, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\", \"score\": 0.9687098981136054, \"rank\": 0.03230079711826201, \"text\": \"Muslim\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\"}, {\"begin\": 1160, \"end\": 1166, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.6950629566232579, \"rank\": 0.4293890195700075, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Anna Blus, Amnesty's women's rights researcher in Europe, said: 'Banning French athletes from competing with sports hijabs at the Olympic and Paralympic Games makes a mockery of claims that Paris 2024 is the first \\\"Gender Equal Olympics\\\".\", \"from\": 1175, \"to\": 1413, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1175, \"end\": 1179, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Freud\", \"score\": 0.8654485817150324, \"rank\": 0.15546689938854924, \"text\": \"Anna\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Freud\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Freud\"}, {\"begin\": 1248, \"end\": 1254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.6950629566232579, \"rank\": 0.4293890195700075, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1317, \"end\": 1333, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999996220299895, \"rank\": 2.597642887712772e-07, \"text\": \"Paralympic Games\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 1365, \"end\": 1375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3209974138860086e-15, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France does not ban hijabs in public spaces.\", \"from\": 1415, \"to\": 1459, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1415, \"end\": 1421, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999815433468716, \"rank\": 1.8045001202915305e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But its policies on the headscarf can be confusing.\", \"from\": 1460, \"to\": 1511, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A law passed in 2010 prohibits the wearing of any face-covering headgear.\", \"from\": 1513, \"to\": 1586, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This included masks,\\u00a0balaclavas,\\u00a0niq\\u0101bs\\u00a0and other veils covering the face.\", \"from\": 1588, \"to\": 1662, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But because the hijab does not cover a person's face, it is allowed.\", \"from\": 1663, \"to\": 1731, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2023, France also decided to ban public school students from wearing the abaya\\u00a0- a long dress or robe popular among women in certain Muslim cultures  'It lays bare the racist gender discrimination that underpins access to sport in the country.'\", \"from\": 1733, \"to\": 1980, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1742, \"end\": 1748, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999815433468716, \"rank\": 1.8045001202915305e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1869, \"end\": 1875, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\", \"score\": 0.9687098981136054, \"rank\": 0.03230079711826201, \"text\": \"Muslim\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She added: 'Discriminatory rules policing what women wear are a violation of Muslim women's and girls' human rights and have a devastating impact on their participation in sport, blocking efforts to make sports more inclusive and more accessible.'\", \"from\": 1982, \"to\": 2229, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2059, \"end\": 2065, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\", \"score\": 0.9687098981136054, \"rank\": 0.03230079711826201, \"text\": \"Muslim\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French sports minister\\u00a0Amelie Oudea-Castera barred French athletes from wearing the hijab, saying they are bound by the country's strict separation of religion and state.\", \"from\": 2231, \"to\": 2401, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2231, \"end\": 2237, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.6950629566232579, \"rank\": 0.4293890195700075, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'What does that mean?\", \"from\": 2403, \"to\": 2424, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That means a ban on any type of proselytising,' she told French TV.\", \"from\": 2425, \"to\": 2492, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2482, \"end\": 2488, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.6950629566232579, \"rank\": 0.4293890195700075, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'That means absolute neutrality in public services, the French team will not wear the headscarf.'\", \"from\": 2494, \"to\": 2591, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2550, \"end\": 2556, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.6950629566232579, \"rank\": 0.4293890195700075, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Proselytising is the act of attempting to change people's religious or political beliefs.\", \"from\": 2593, \"to\": 2682, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The values of Olympism are excellence, respect and friendship.\", \"from\": 2684, \"to\": 2746, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The host country above all should honour these.\", \"from\": 2747, \"to\": 2794, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But#Franceis the only country in Europe that specifically bans sport hijabs#ParisOlympics2024#Paris2024\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0091\\u0087https://t.co/u0o2sNFtBepic.twitter.com/mjqsXlebtF  In France, the prohibition on Muslim women from wearing any form of religious headgear extends far beyond the Olympic and Paralympic Games.\", \"from\": 2795, \"to\": 3092, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2956, \"end\": 2962, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999815433468716, \"rank\": 1.8045001202915305e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2983, \"end\": 2989, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\", \"score\": 0.9687098981136054, \"rank\": 0.03230079711826201, \"text\": \"Muslim\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bans on hijabs are in place across several sports including football, basketball and volleyball, at both professional and amateur levels.\", \"from\": 3094, \"to\": 3231, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Amnesty International, along with 10 other sports and human rights groups, had earlier appealed to the IOC to intervene on the ban.\", \"from\": 3233, \"to\": 3364, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3233, \"end\": 3254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amnesty_International\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.511111018029464e-15, \"text\": \"Amnesty International\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amnesty_International\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amnesty_International\"}, {\"begin\": 3336, \"end\": 3339, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4275057658665066e-28, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the committee responded that overturning the policy was beyond its remit.\", \"from\": 3366, \"to\": 3443, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Foune Diawara, co-president of the football collective Hijabeuses, told Amnesty: 'Our fight is not political or religious but centered on our human right to participate in sports.'\", \"from\": 3445, \"to\": 3625, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3451, \"end\": 3458, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manthia_Diawara\", \"score\": 0.9999999999899956, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Diawara\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manthia_Diawara\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manthia_Diawara\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Former NBA player Tariq Abdul-Wahad, and former English cricketer Azeem Rafiq are among those who have urged France to overturn its decision.\", \"from\": 3627, \"to\": 3768, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3634, \"end\": 3637, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 0.9999999999809006, \"rank\": 1.4032502224037362e-11, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 3645, \"end\": 3662, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tariq_Abdul-Wahad\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tariq Abdul-Wahad\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tariq_Abdul-Wahad\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tariq_Abdul-Wahad\"}, {\"begin\": 3693, \"end\": 3704, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Azeem_Rafiq\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Azeem Rafiq\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Azeem_Rafiq\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Azeem_Rafiq\"}, {\"begin\": 3736, \"end\": 3742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999815433468716, \"rank\": 1.8045001202915305e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics have already been laced with controversy amid high levels of E.Coli bacteria in the River Seine.\", \"from\": 3770, \"to\": 3879, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3844, \"end\": 3850, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Escherichia_coli\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"E.Coli\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Escherichia_coli\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Escherichia_coli\"}, {\"begin\": 3867, \"end\": 3878, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The levels are so high that testing concludes it is not safe for swimming most days.\", \"from\": 3880, \"to\": 3964, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hundreds of\\u00a0homeless\\u00a0people have also been banished from the French capital in the preparation for the iconic sporting event, leading to accusations that the government is trying to 'sanitise' the city.\", \"from\": 3966, \"to\": 4168, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4027, \"end\": 4033, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.6950629566232579, \"rank\": 0.4293890195700075, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Get in touch with our news team by emailing us atwebnews@metro.co.uk.\", \"from\": 4170, \"to\": 4239, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4227, \"end\": 4238, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metro_(British_newspaper)\", \"score\": 0.9993608704168107, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"metro.co.uk\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metro_(British_newspaper)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metro_(British_newspaper)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For more stories like this,check our news page.\", \"from\": 4241, \"to\": 4288, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ArrowMORE:Rafael Nadal makes retirement decision after beating Bjorn Borg's son in Bastad  ArrowMORE:'She's not the wicked stepmother': How Queen Camilla won over her critics  ArrowMORE:Police forces in the UK have got away with racism for too long  Stay on top of the headlines with daily email updates.\", \"from\": 4290, \"to\": 4594, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4300, \"end\": 4312, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rafael Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}, {\"begin\": 4353, \"end\": 4363, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bj\\u00f6rn_Borg\", \"score\"